[[Image:Josan new ISC.jpg|thumb|right|New Jozan rug]]

'''Jozan rugs''' are made in the surroundings of the village [[Jowzan, Hamadan|Jozan]] in the [[Iran]]ian [[Malayer]] area. Jozan rugs are quality rugs of the [[Sarouk Rug|Sarouk]] type often with designs as early 20th century Sarouks. Jozan rugs are often called Jozan Sarouk or Malayer Sarouk in trade. In recent production the finer qualities are labelled Jozan and the less finer knotted are labelled [[Malayer]].

They are [[double-weft]]ed on a cotton foundation.

